<HR size="1" color="#a62a2a">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Hail all.<P>I come here today to post on a most disturbing incident which occurred on the Povar server on Monday afternoon. That was the day, where after 6 days of straight camping by Crystaltiger, a noble and caring cleric of Heroes Unlimited, Ragefire was KS'd fom her by the Utopians. Let me explain the situation.<P>Crystaltiger and various members of our guild allies set-up camp in skyfire beginning last Wednesday, February 6. Finally, Ragefire spawned yesterday afternoon, February 11. Heroes Unlimited and allies quickly began to gather the forces necessary to dispatch rage. Another guild, not a member of our alliance, the Utopians, offered assistance in killing the dragon, which was welcomed, as we assumed their intentions were friendly. This, as you will see, was not the case.<P>The human ragefire was pulled and quickly killed. Once the dragon spawned, however, most of our forces were wiped out. This, however, did not disuade us. Crystaltiger and friends quickly began rezzing fallen comrades, to make another run at the dragon. In the time it took to rez all the fallen and rebuff, the Utopians had been gathering forces at the BW zone to defeat ragefire for their own cleric, the same person who had previously offered assistance in slaying the dragon. Before anyone knew what happened, ragefire was dead, and the utopian cleric had the necessary component to complete the epic, while Crystaltiger was left with nothing to show for the 6 days she spend camping the spot.<P>GM's were called in, who basically said "tough luck, Crystaltiger". <P>Now, to me this is a disgusting situation which nobody should have to put themselves through. Crystaltiger spent 6 days without anything but a cat-nap, only to have rage stolen from her when he actually did pop. The Utopians should be ashamed of their actions. When the GM's confronted members of the utopians, they lied and changed their answers to the questions presented them.<P>Luckily, one member of our alliance was logging the entire event, from the moments before the human ragefire was pulled, to after the dragon was ks'd, and throughout the entire meeting with both sides. It will take some time to gather all of the information, but once it is, we will be posting the log in various message boards throughout the EQ community, as well as sending it by email to Verant itself. <P>I'm sorry for taking up so much of your time, but I feel that this had to be made public. Thank you for your time, and I hope that nothing like this ever happens to you.<P>Sincerely,<BR>Anthonius Throneblade<BR>Proud Paladin Officer of Heroes Unlimited
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#a62a2a">
